data.name: RegionHelpRichText.Text
data.value:
Click on the map to set a point in the region.
Drag to the next location, then click to set the point.
Right-click to end drawing the region.
Shift+click on a landform coastline to begin snapping the region to the coastline of the landform.
Drag down then shift+click on the coastline to snap the region to the east (right) coastline of the landform.
Drag up then shift+click on the coastline to snap the region to the west (left) coastline of the landform.
To snap a region to the north (top) or south (bottom) of a landform, shift+click on the east (right) coastline, then drag left and up or down to the opposite coastline, and shift+click.
